All heads of procurement in accounting units in ministries, their departments and state corporations have been told to step aside. Their deputies will take over. In a statement to newsrooms, governemnt spokesperson Mwenda Njoka said the officers are required to submit their personal information by June 8 to the Head of Public Service. "The information sought [should] include the assets they own, liabilities and previous records of service," Njoka said. The move comes days after President Uhuru Kenyatta ordered the fresh vetting of public officers Read: More heads to roll as purge on corrupt officers hots up Click here for more political news